activities.notes:
The talk will be given in portuguese.
The idea is to start applying the finite volume method over the bidimensional transient head conduction equation, and then immediately jump into implementation details. For more information, please, check the project on https://github.com/tarcisiofischer/heat_diffusion_experiment/blob/master/README.ipynb

I hope the talk will be interesting for the audience with the following backgrounds:
1) Undergrad/Graduated engineering students that will probably have to code similar projects on future;
2) Students and professionals that are more used to matlab/c++/fortran and want to see a python project in practice;
3) Students and professionals that use nonlinear solvers for other problems may be interested about the petsc4py vs scipy implementation comparison.

activities.bio:
I've always been a lover of science and technology. Since the first time I read Carl Sagan's Contact to my yearning for learning (currently focusing on NLP). I graduated in 2015 from the Federal University of Santa Catarina with double honors (highest GPA and faculty elected "best student") after a one year exchange program at the University of Toronto on a full-scholarship. During my academic period, I had the chance to do multiple internships in parallel (and during the summer break) in many areas. After graduation I discovered the area of Data Science and since then have focused all my efforts on building my career.

Since then, I had the opportunity to lead the data science team at Chaordic, the largest online retail recommendation system in Brazil. There I was able to apply the SciPy stack to problems such as:

- Develop new product recommendation algorithms for our E-commerce customers;
- Provide ad-hoc analyses to find insights from our data;
- Design and monitor competitive A/B experiments devised to validate our systems performance in the face of competition.
- Internal A/B testing tool using the SciPy and Jupyter stack;
- OMNI channel recommender systems;
- Mixed collaborative filtering and content based algorithms;
- Continuous space parameter optimization using exploration/exploitation policies;
- Bandit algorithms for online optimization;
- LNC's Machine Learning Challenge for talent acquisition: https://goo.gl/EVdXsH

Today I work at Code:Nation building predictive models and chat bots to help developers skyrocket their careers.
